In six states  Alaska Colorado Louisiana Mississippi California and Texas  fentanyl fatalities increased nearly fivefold according to the study.
Meanwhile the fentanyl nightmare is driving an explosion of drug overdoses in the South.
Overdose deaths reported each year have risen more than 70 during the past five years in Alabama Arkansas Louisiana Mississippi and Tennessee according to CDC data analyzed by The Tennessean.
Those five states combined reported nearly 4100 overdose deaths in 2016. By 2020  the most recent year on record  the same states reported nearly 7000 overdose deaths.
In some states a life-saving drug is just a few clicks away.
The anti-overdose medication naloxone also known by the brand name Narcan is for sale at NaloxoneExchange.com which is run by a fast-growing startup that expanded into Tennessee in 2019.
Naloxone is largely viewed as a front-line defense to the opioid crisis because it can be injected or inhaled to reverse an opioid overdose in the moment.
Loved ones who lost someone to fentanyl poisoning have started nonprofits  not only to get the word out about access to Narcan but to spread word about the epidemic and even offer fentanyl paper test strips which are an easy and inexpensive method to avert a drug overdose. They can detect the presence of fentanyl in pills powder or injectables.
