How to help during an overdose
If there is an immediate health crisis call 911 or go to the emergency room.
Metro Public Health has also identified several avenues for assistance in the case of a drug problem.
247 crisis line Call the Tennessee Redline at 1-800-889-9789 for information and referrals for help. It is coordinated by the Tennessee Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Service.
Narcotics Anonymous Nashville www.na.org or www.nanashville.org for information on the nonprofit. The organization meets regularly to help others in their recovery process by providing a peer support network.
Smart Recovery www.smartrecovery.org. A nationwide nonprofit organization that offers free support groups including sponsor meetings online meetings and 247 chat room forums.
More information is available at www.nashville.govHealth-Department.
