A longtime Tennessee doctor who moved to Indiana after five patients died of overdoses in less than a year will spend years in prison on federal drug charges.
Dr. Darrel Rinehart 66 who ran a clinic in Columbia for decades was indicted on 19 counts of distribution of a controlled substance in March 2019.
He was sentenced this week to three years in prison for unlawfully distributing controlled substances according to a news release from the Department of Justice.
At least five of Rineharts patients suffered fatal overdoses that were partially or wholly caused by drugs he prescribed between March 2015 and January 2016 according to public records.
