NASHVILLE Tenn.--A Nashville woman is facing multiple charges in the city and in Kentucky following the overdose death of a Lebanon woman in Kentucky.
The Metro Nashville Police Department MNPD reports 21-year-old Hannah Forkum was arrested on Wednesday during an undercover drug buy at the Motel 6 on Stewarts Ferry Pike.
Forkum was caught with 25 grams of fentanyl 27 grams of meth laced with fentanyl and 7 grams of black tar heroin.
Forkum is also accused of selling a deadly cocktail of drugs to a Lebanon woman at the hotel. According to police 21-year-old Baylee McClanahan purchased the narcotics from Forkum at the motel before overdosing on them while visiting a friend in Kentucky on Tuesday.
Police also arrested three men in Forkum's hotel room each wanted for outstanding warrants on separate charges. Forkum is facing charges in Kentucky for 2nd degree murder in addition to possessing fentanyl heroin and meth for resale. A handgun was also found in her hotel room at the time of her arrest.
