Ryan Dunleavy of Brentwood was found the morning of June 15 in the venue's Manchester's campgrounds his autopsy results show. He was transported to Unity Medical Center in Manchester where he was pronounced dead.
According to a toxicology report Dunleavy had drugs including fentanyl MDMA ecstasy and clozapine in his system when he died. Autopsy results show Dunleavy's manner of death was accidental.
In some of the overdose cases across Tennessee authorities have arrested the decedent's dealer. It's part of a strategy to fight the opioid epidemic.
One month before Dunleavy overdosed  after nearly a year and a half of extensive investigative work  Metro Nashville police charged 32-year-old Christopher James Floyd with murder in connection to a woman's 2017 death.
Authorities said Roberts provided the mix of heroin and fentanyl that killed Sara Roberts who fatally overdosed at the East Thompson Lane home where she lived with her mother.
An autopsy found the 33-year-old Nashville woman died of acute drug toxicity from a combination of alcohol and heroin laced with fentanyl.
Floyd remained jailed in Davidson County Wednesday awaiting trial on more than 100000 bond.
