In just two years fentanyl poisoning deaths have doubled across the nation and in 30 states including Tennessee deaths have more than doubled according to a new analysis from Families Against Fentanyl.
The Volunteer state is among 20 states with the highest number of fentanyl deaths last year according to the nonprofit's analysis calculated using data from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention from May 2019-2021.
