Police have arrested and charged a fourth person with second degree murder in connection with the fatal Fentanyl overdose of a 38-year-old woman in Hermitage last year.
Najir Ellis was arrested in Clarksville this week in connection with the death of Nicole Aylward.
Aylward died April 3 2015 from a Fentanyl and heroin overdose at Shannon Wise and Joseph Thompson's Central Pike apartment. Both Wise and Thompson were immediately charged with second degree murder and a number of felony drug charges.
